# Web testing bar

Full reference: [docs/domain/web-testing.md](../../docs/domain/web-testing.md).

## Rules

1. **MSW only for new tests** — `server.use(handlers)` from `web/src/test/handlers/`. No new `vi.spyOn(globalThis, "fetch")`.
2. **Register handlers in integration tests** — `server.use(...appDefaultHandlers(), …)` for task-pages and task-create. MSW uses `onUnhandledRequest: "bypass"` globally so legacy `vi.spyOn(fetch)` component tests still work.
3. **No bare sleeps** — `vi.useFakeTimers()` or `createDeferred()`; never `setTimeout` or `new Promise(() => {})`.
4. **Project placement** — `unit` / `components` / `app` / `task-pages` / `task-create` / `settings` / `projects` / `worktrees` per `web/vitest.workspace.ts`. `<App />` and pages belong in the matching full-app project.
5. **≤ 500 lines** per `*.test.{ts,tsx}`.
6. **Keep tests fast** — prefer handlers + `renderHook` over full-app renders when the behaviour is local.

## Harness tiers

Use the smallest harness that covers the behaviour under test. Defined in [`appHarness.tsx`](../../web/src/test/integration/appHarness.tsx).

| Harness | Mounts | Use for |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `renderApp()` / `renderAppAt(entries)` | Full `<App />` — bootstrap, SSE, shell, lazy routes | Routing, bootstrap, 404, cross-feature navigation (`test-app`) |
| `renderTasksHome()` / `renderTasksAt(entries)` | Tasks shell only — home, drafts, create modals | Create-task flows, drafts page (`test-task-create`, drafts in `test-task-pages`) |
| Direct `render(<Page />)` + MSW | Single page component | Task detail/cycle/event pages when routing is not under test |

`renderTasksHome` omits `useBootstrap`, `useTaskEventStream`, `AppShell`, and lazy routes. Do not use `renderApp` to test a create modal or drafts list.

Always call `setupAppTest()` in `beforeEach` and `server.use(...appDefaultHandlers(), …)` for the endpoints the test hits.

## Good

```ts
beforeEach(() => {
  setupAppTest();
  server.use(...appDefaultHandlers(), tasksListEmpty());
});
renderTasksHome();
```

## Bad

```ts
vi.spyOn(globalThis, "fetch").mockImplementation(async (input) => { /* 40 lines */ });
renderApp(); // full shell to open a modal
```
